<subSubSection id="D56511DB31BA8DE5B47C45C7B8EA7282" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="67E08776EA2D5C7935E30391FA684852" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E15BD468D19A4C46999757360C8D7DD0" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="B49FF0A72A65649AD42DFEF405C6FFC6" class="Aves" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Lepanthes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lepanthes jimburae" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jimburae">
<emphasis id="EC358166D4F34D0A6ECF9871E52B248B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Lepanthes jimburae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Luer &amp; Hirtz, but can be distinguished by the smaller plants that are less than 3 cm tall (vs. up to 4 cm tall); the shorter inflorescence that is less than 4 cm long (vs. inflorescence up to 10 cm long), the shorter dorsal sepal with a shorter sepaline tail (6.0 mm vs. 9.0 mm long), the apical lobe of the petals ovate and lower lobe triangular-oblong (vs. petals with subequal, obliquely triangular, acute lobes).
</paragraph>
