<subSubSection id="0A5713745877B0FB8F7025A0F098B251" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="AE95D00406BD348437C0932B971B5769" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9700ABC7F347711CE7B405C51077ECB7" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
<taxonomicName id="48D23B80CB04CFB2EDFECEE058D398F6" authorityName="Tobar &amp; M. F. Lopez" authorityYear="2021" class="Aves" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Lepanthes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lepanthes oro-lojaensis" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oro-lojaensis">
<emphasis id="9A4816198E217E5A4A3051227C750657" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Lepanthes oro-lojaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from a single locality on the border between El Oro and Loja provinces (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="30C092A5C1117FC80335C5002BDF2BC6" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Geographical distribution of the three new species of Lepanthes microprsartima Tobar &amp; M. J. Gavil. (black hexagon, three collections), Lepanthes caranqui Tobar &amp; Monteros (black triangle, two collections) and Lepanthes oro-lojaensis Tobar &amp; M. F. Lopez (black pentagon, one collection)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.180.62671.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/574520" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">4</figureCitation>
). The species was collected in a small patch of scrubs, growing on 
<taxonomicName id="95D6DEA0A670FF2FF2ABB2C942CE8237" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Berberis" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Berberis lutea" order="Ranunculales" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lutea">
<emphasis id="5B79317C22868D0A765479210B5B6C76" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Berberis lutea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Ruiz &amp; Pav. (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B9D202C5EC2FA2F952BFEB839504D5D6" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Landscape near to Cerro de Arcos, where Lepanthes oro-lojaensis was collected, in El Oro Province A natural vegetation remnants B areas where Pinus have been planted." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.180.62671.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/574521" pageId="0" pageNumber="111">5</figureCitation>
), which is a representative species of the evergreen forest formation (BsSn01) according to 
<bibRefCitation id="E4E6A7AA30D970D3CEB35D0BACD8B365" author="Ministerio del Ambiente del Ecuador" journalOrPublisher="Novon" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" publicationUrl="https://www.ambiente.gob.ec/wp-content/uploads/downloads/2012/09/LEYENDA-ECOSISTEMAS_ECUADOR_2.pdf" refId="B16" refString="Ministerio del Ambiente del Ecuador, 2013. Sistema de Clasificacion de los Ecosistemas del Ecuador Continental. Subsecretaria de Patrimonio Natural, 300 pp. https://www.ambiente.gob.ec/wp-content/uploads/downloads/2012/09/LEYENDA-ECOSISTEMAS_ECUADOR_2.pdf" title="Sistema de Clasificacion de los Ecosistemas del Ecuador Continental. Subsecretaria de Patrimonio Natural, 300 pp." url="https://www.ambiente.gob.ec/wp-content/uploads/downloads/2012/09/LEYENDA-ECOSISTEMAS_ECUADOR_2.pdf" year="2013">Ministerio del Ambiente del Ecuador (2013)</bibRefCitation>
. This type of vegetation is found in sites protected from the wind and desiccation, such as glacial valleys, ravines or under large blocks of rock, which allow them to maintain a higher humidity than the surrounding vegetation and favors the presence of some epiphytes (
<bibRefCitation id="F974EFEE7720A5881E414E1598497BE2" author="Sierra, R" editor="Sierra, R" journalOrPublisher="Proyecto INEFAN / GEF-BIRF y EcoCiencia" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" pagination="29 - 54" refId="B19" refString="Sierra, R, Ceron, CE, Palacios, W, Valencia, R, 1999. Criterios para la clasificacion de la vegetacion del Ecuador. In: Sierra, R, Ed., Propuesta preliminar de un sistema de clasificacion de vegetacion para el Ecuador continental. Proyecto INEFAN/GEF-BIRF y EcoCiencia: 29 - 54" title="Criterios para la clasificacion de la vegetacion del Ecuador." volumeTitle="Propuesta preliminar de un sistema de clasificacion de vegetacion para el Ecuador continental." year="1999">Sierra et al. 1999</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="AAFA427351D5843D117BFF865F946595" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.180.62671.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/574520" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" start="Figure 4" startId="F4">
